        <h2>Why Protein is Key</h2>
        <p>Protein is essential for muscle repair and growth. In a vegan diet, you can get high-quality protein from foods like lentils, chickpeas, tofu, and tempeh.</p>

        <h2>Balancing Macronutrients</h2>
        <p>A balanced diet includes the right proportion of protein, carbohydrates, and fats. Focus on whole, nutrient-dense foods to get the energy you need.</p>

        <h2>Top Vegan Foods for Muscle Growth</h2>
        <p>Foods like quinoa, seitan, and nuts are packed with protein and nutrients. Combine these with a variety of fruits and vegetables for a well-rounded diet.</p>
